<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Robaina Stresses Strengthening Relations With Exiles </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2602131094 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1000 
GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2602131094 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by reporter Roberto Canela] </F>
  [Text] Cuban Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina Gonzalez has 
told the Pinar del Rio newspaper EL GUERRILLERO that the 
nation-exile community conference scheduled for next April seeks 
to return a normal communication process to relations between 
Cuba and the exile community. He added that all countries 
throughout the world have relations with their residents abroad, 
and Cuba should be no exception. 
  Robaina explained that we must reestablish normal relations 
with our community abroad, and that this relationship must 
include all residents abroad, not just those in the United 
States. He said it is impossible to speak of an opening to the 
world without including the existence of our fellow citizens 
globally. He added that it is not Cuba that excludes the 
hostile, aggressive ones. They exclude themselves. 
  Robaina concluded by saying that our foreign policy is 
integral to a people and a revolution accustomed to surprises 
and to gaining power where it appears not to exist. If foreign 
policy can do this, it is a reflection of the desires of the 
people and the Revolution. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

