<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Supply of Petroleum `Confirmed' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2502221094 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1800 
GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2502221094 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with Pedro Perez, director of the Cuban import </F>
company, Cubametales, by reporter Carlos Santana Ojeda -- place 
and date not given -- live or recorded] 
  [Text] [Santana] What can you tell us, Pedro, about this 
report on the sale of Colombian crude oil to Cuba? 
  [Perez] I can tell you that for many years Cubametales [Cuba 
Metal Import Enterprise] has been holding talks with the 
Colombian company Copetrol [expansion unknown] for direct supply 
of Colombian crude oil to Cuba because this is a product we know 
very well, having been receiving it through negotiations with 
other commercial companies. 
  We recently held a new meeting to discuss the possibility of 
this sale under normal market conditions. The Colombian 
officials are studying this, and we are waiting for the final 
results of those studies. This is the situation today concerning 
the possible supply of Colombian petroleum to our country. 
  [Santana] Pedro, I have an AFP report that says Colombia 
will 
sell from 15,000 to 20,000 barrels of petroleum to Cuba daily as 
of next June. Can this be taken as a confirmation of the 
situation? 
  [Perez] Well, that is a point of reference because petroleum 
amounts are usually determined according to shipments received 
at port, not according to daily delivery of products. In any 
case, I believe that is an amount we can assimilate. It will be 
so -- or it can be so -- if we reach an agreement. 
  [Santana] Well, you have just heard the news we received 
here 
at our studio confirmed by Pedro Perez, director of Cubametales. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

