<H3> <TI>   Beijing Invites Cuban Business Participation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2602164694 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1500 GMT 
26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2602164694 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] (Li Hu Wa), responsible for the Beijing town hall 
and Beijing's economic reform, today stated that Cuban economic 
and commercial representatives are welcome to participate in 
business operations in Beijing. 
  (Li Hu Wa) extended the invitation during an interview with 
PRENSA LATINA when he said that cooperation with other countries 
is the main objective of Beijing officials. 
  (Li Hu Wa) referred to cooperation with Cuba when he 
stressed 
the effort being made to accelerate the reform and opening 
process, the objectives of which are cooperation with foreign 
investing companies and modernization of national institutions. 
  Economic and commercial relations between China and Cuba 
have 
increased over the past few years with the exchange of 
machinery, foodstuffs, medicines, and medical equipment. 

</TEXT>

