<H3> <TI>   `Most Critical' Section Worked on </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2702161294 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 1515 
GMT 27 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2702161294 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Radio ACIR Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] After 48 hours of tension and silence Manuel 
Camacho Solis, peace and reconciliation commissioner for 
Chiapas, and the Zapatist National Liberation Army [EZLN] 
released a brief communique disclosing that they are currently 
working on the most critical part of the agreements but that 
they expect positive results. 
  For eight days since the opening of the talks Camacho has 
been unable to leave the area. There have been reports to the 
effect that the situation inside the capital [as heard] is 
difficult. 
  Meanwhile, the Indian Revolutionary Clandestine Committee 
General Command issued a text asserting that to achieve free and 
democratic elections, the head of the federal Executive Branch 
must resign and a transition government be formed. It also 
calls for truly free and democratic elections with equal rights 
and duties for the political organizations that are struggling 
for power. 
  Strangely, however, the communique signed by Subcommander 
Marcos is written in biblical language; it is as if they 
extracted their words and phrases from the Bible. It is a very, 
very strange communique. 

</TEXT>

