<H3> <TI>   Menem Visit to Spain Previewed; Comments on Health </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2802090394 Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network in Spanish 0700 GMT 
28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2802090394 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Argentine President Carlos Saul Menem begins a 
three-day official visit to Spain today. He had to postpone the 
visit twice: first because of the death of Don Juan de Borbon 
[King Juan Carlos's father] and then because of the heart attack 
he suffered. [passage omitted] 
  Jose Manuel Martin Meden reports on this visit: 
  [Martin Meden] [Passage omitted] Menem arrives in Madrid 
with 
his political horizon clear after the agreement with the 
opposition for a constitutional reform that will enable him to 
be re-elected and to govern until the year 2000 if he wins a 
majority in 1995. In statements for Radiotelevision Espanola, 
the president of Argentina confirms his good health and his 
readiness to continue as president. 
  [Begin Menem recording] I am much better than before the 
operation. I shall face it with the same passion, the same 
enthusiasm, the same spirit with which I have done everything in 
my life and, of course, with a small quantity of ability. [end 
recording] 
  [Martin Meden] [Passage omitted] President Menem says that 
he 
is convinced that, through negotiation, in the year 2000 the 
Malvinas [Falkland] Islands will be Argentine again. 
  [Begin Menem recording] I have the intuition -- and in 
intuition there is also some share of of intelligence, of wisdom 
-- that in the year 2000 the Malvinas Islands will be in the 
possession of Argentina again. [end recording] [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

