<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   Leaders of Indian Organization Attack FSLN Activists </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2702003094 Managua Radio Sandino in Spanish 1200 GMT 24 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2702003094 </F>
<F P=104>  Managua Radio Sandino </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Jose Gart from the "Radio Events" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Yatama [Indian military organization] leaders 
attacked 50 FSLN activists following a rally to close an FSLN 
[Sandinist National Liberation Front] political campaign in 
Puerto Cabezas. FSLN candidate (Evelyn Watler) was beaten up, 
and a window in a station wagon owned by Victor Espinoza, FSLN 
political secretary in Puerto Cabezas, was smashed. 
  Brooklyn Rivera, YATAMA's top leader and currently director 
of INDERA [Nicaraguan Institute for the Development of the 
Autonomous Regions of the Atlantic Coast], headed the attack. 
Alfonso Smith, governor of the North Atlantic Autonomous 
Region, Kenneth Bush, the Government Ministry's delegate, and 
other YATAMA activists also lead the criminal action. 
  The FSLN issued a statement on Radio Caribe on the night of 
23 February repudiating the attitude of the YATAMA leaders and 
urging authorities to restore order in the North Atlantic 
Autonomous Region. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

