<F P=100> Ecuador </F>
<H3> <TI>   Energy Minister Announces Reduction in Oil Production </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2802000194 Quito Voz de los Andes in Spanish 2300 GMT 24 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2802000194 </F>
<F P=104>  Quito Voz de los Andes </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Voz Andes" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Francisco Acosta, energy and mines minister, 
announced that Ecuador must reduce oil production because the 
country will no longer be able to use the Colombian trans-Andean 
pipeline. Acosta reported that Colombian Petroleum Enterprise 
will not be able to lease the pipeline to Ecuador to transport 
its crude oil because it is designed to carry 25 degrees API 
crude, not 29 degrees API, which is the specific weight Ecuador 
will soon begin to produce. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

