<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S. Bid Result Partnership Proposed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2502215294 Sao Paulo FOLHA DE SAO PAULO in Portuguese 24 
Feb 94 Section 2 p 4 </F>

<F P=103> PY2502215294 </F>
<F P=104>  Sao Paulo FOLHA DE SAO PAULO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Argentine Defense Minister Oscar Camilion yesterday 
proposed to Embraer [Brazilian Aeronautics Company] 
Superintendent Ozires Silva a cooperation agreement should one 
of the two countries be awarded the U.S. Government bid to 
supply 800 aircraft for military training purposes. The 
contract is worth $4.5 billion. Camilion visited the Embraer 
premises yesterday. 
  FOLHA was unable to contact Ozires yesterday. Embraer Social 
Communications Manager Mario Galvao was unaware of Embraer's 
decision regarding the offer. Embraer is participating in the 
bid with the Super Tucano turbo-prop aircraft. The Argentine 
FMA [Military Aircraft Factory] will participate in the same bid 
with the IA-63 Pampa jet. The results of the bid will be 
disclosed at the end of the year. 

</TEXT>

