<F P=100> Colombia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Police Forces Deployed to Capital Prior to Elections </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2702033094 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 0130 GMT 27 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2702033094 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Alexandra Ortiz for the "TV Today" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Starting today and continuing until 13 March, 
members of the police force, the Administrative Department of 
Security, and the Judicial Police and Investigations Directorate 
will conduct joint operations in Santa Fe de Bogota to counter 
guerrilla activities. 
  Nearly 1,000 men from the state security organizations have 
been deployed to four areas in Santa Fe de Bogota. Elite units 
will remain posted at the entrances to the capital to prevent 
guerrillas from reaching downtown Santa Fe de Bogota. Raids 
will be conducted on the city's outskirts, where intelligence 
officials report the presence of subversives. 
  There will be air and sea surveillance during demonstrations 
and political gatherings, and uniformed personnel will be in the 
67 campaign centers 24 hours a day. 
  [Begin Police Commander Enrique Montenegro recording] If we 
are able to accomplish this, we can guarantee relative security 
during the election campaign. [end recording] 
  Public order forces will be deployed and security measures 
will be adopted in all cities to counter the guerrilla actions. 

</TEXT>

