<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Neo-Nazis Claim Contacts With World Trade Center Bombers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2602174694 Sao Paulo FOLHA DE SAO PAULO in Portuguese 24 
Feb 94 p 3 </F>

<F P=103> PY2602174694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sao Paulo FOLHA DE SAO PAULO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On 23 February, the Teotonio Vilela Human Rights 
Committee informed the Attorney General's Office about the 
creation of a new neo-Nazi group -- "White Power" [preceding two 
words in English] -- in Florianopolis (Santa Catarina State). 
The group says it has created "shooting blacks week." 
  The group threatens to attack with bombs sites regularly 
visited by blacks. In publications known as "skinzines," the 
group reports it is settling in Florianopolis to "defend racial 
purity and preserve social order." It proposes "expelling 
blacks from Brazil." 
  Councilman Marcio de Souza (Workers Party) sent the 
committee 
a publication in which the neo-Nazis promise to blow up the 
building where his office is located. 
  The messages are signed by pen names such as "Black Killer" 
[preceding two words in English]. It is stated in them that 
people involved in the bomb explosion at the World Trade Center 
building in New York have been contacted by the group and asked 
to come to Santa Catarina to conduct similar attacks. The 
Attorney General's Office will ask Federal Police to begin 
investigating the charges. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

