<H3> <TI>   Havana Reports NATO Announcement of Downed Serbian Aircraft </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2802154094 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1502 GMT 
28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2802154094 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Four Serbian aircraft have been shot down by U.S. 
F-16 fighters today near Banja Luka in northwestern Bosnia, in 
keeping with a UN Security Council resolution that forbids any 
and all flights in the skies over Bosnia, according to a NATO 
military spokesman. 
  This is the first time NATO planes have opened fire in 
Bosnia, after the Serb planes ignored the F-16s' orders to land. 
NATO planes have been patrolling Bosnia daily since April 1993, 
with a view to enforcing respect of UN Security Council 
Resolution No. 816, which forbids any and all flights in Bosnian 
airspace, according to the spokesman. 
  Meanwhile, a spokesman for the UN High Commissioner for 
Refugees [word indistinct] said all humanitarian flights to 
Sarajevo have been suspended, as has all movement toward areas 
controlled by the Serbs. 

</TEXT>

