<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bishop Ruiz on Chiapas Negotiations Progress </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2802143894 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2802143894 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by correspondent Francisco Rubio; from the "Good </F>
Morning From Mexico" newscast] 
  [Text] The bishop of San Cristobal de las Casas, Samuel 
Ruiz Garcia, has announced that the draft documents that will be 
entitled Commitments for an Honorable Peace, Commitment for 
Peace, and Peace Declaration, are in their final phase. 
  He denied that national issues such as democracy and 
modification of constitutional Article 27, which deals with 
agrarian laws, have delayed the negotiations for peace. 
  [Begin Ruiz recording] There are 34 commitments. Two of 
these commitments are not binding. They have to do with 
democracy. From the beginning it was a known fact that they do 
not form part of an agreement, strictly speaking, but that they 
are an opinion made known to the national community. It is 
expected that this opinion should have an impact on this 
community. [end recording] 
  Ruiz said that some 10 or 12 points are yet to be negotiated 
before an agreement is reached. Of these points, four or five 
are of secondary importance. 
  [Begin Ruiz recording] The others have a certain level of 
importance but because of linguistic difficulties they are still 
being discussed. They are not fundamental for reaching an 
agreement. We could say that a significant agreement has been 
reached already. [end recording] 
  More than 72 hours after the doors of the peace cathedral 
were closed -- something that spawned speculation that the peace 
talks had been blocked -- Bishop Samuel Ruiz said that neither 
the commissioner for peace and reconciliation in Chiapas nor the 
Zapatist National Liberation Army have been intransigent. 
  [Begin Ruiz recording] So far there has been intransigence 
neither in the discussions of the agreements that are to be 
approved nor in the position of either side. [end recording] 
  This information was provided during a news conference that 
Bishop Samuel Ruiz held alone with reporters. He explained that 
the final text of the agreements could me made known either 
Tuesday [1 March] evening or Wednesday [2 March] morning. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

