<H3> <TI>   President Interviewed on Japanese Investment </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1902134794 Tokyo YOMIURI SHIMBUN in Japanese 18 Feb 94 
Morning Edition p 7 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1902134794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo YOMIURI SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report on interview with President Cesar Gaviria Trujillo </F>
by Kiyoshi Yoshikawa on 16 February; place not given] 
  [Text] Samta Fe de Bogota, 16 Feb -- Colombian President 
Cesar Gaviria Trujillo granted an interview to Japanese 
reporters, including one from YOMIURI SHIMBUN, on 16 February. 
In the interview, the president revealed his plan to visit 
Japan from 26 February to 3 March. He also indicated his 
intention during his visit to urge Japan to invest in Colombia. 
  President Gaviria said: "I have concrete aims for my visit, 
such as promotion of relations with Japan in the technical 
field." The president expressed his hope that Japan's loans will 
be increased to assist Colombia in setting up a research center 
designed to enhance productivity and competitive power in the 
manufacturing industry, as well as in improving production 
facilities in large oil fields. Moreover, he stated that the 
country had no rescheduling (deferring debt repayment) in the 
1980's. The president requested Japan to increase loans, 
saying: "The international financial circles have highly 
evaluated that Colombia has completed repayment of foreign 
debts. I hope that the Japanese financial circle will deepen 
connections with Colombia." 

</TEXT>

