<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Praises Gaviria OAS Candidacy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2402145794 Havana PRENSA LATINA in Spanish 1531 GMT 20 Feb 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PA2402145794 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana PRENSA LATINA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Havana, 20 Feb (PL) -- Foreign Minister Roberto 
Robaina praised Colombian President Cesar Gaviria's candidacy 
for the OAS secretary generalship although he warned Cuba cannot 
support any candidate. 
  Robaina expressed the island's position after newsmen 
consulted him on the subject last night, following a three-day 
visit to the central provinces accompanied by more than 40 
members of the diplomatic corps accredited in this capital. 
  The minister said there is no doubt that President Gaviria 
is 
a man who carries out a mandate and fulfills his 
responsibilities, and he is a man with experience who gives 
guarantees and achieves results. 
  However, he made it clear that Cuba "can hardly say who is 
the best or the worst candidate" because it is not a member of 
that organization. 
  I am fully convinced that the members of that organization 
will know how to evaluate who is the best choice for secretary 
general, he stressed. 
  Havana was expelled from the OAS in 1962 due to the great 
pressure exerted by the United States to isolate from the rest 
of the continent. [sentence as received] 

</TEXT>

