<F P=101> Argentina </F>
<H3> <TI>   Santiago del Estero Workers Stage Protest March 26 Feb </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2802204894 Buenos Aires BUENOS AIRES HERALD in English 27 
Feb 94 p 4 </F>

<F P=103> PY2802204894 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires BUENOS AIRES HERALD </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Santiago del Estero (DYN-NA) -- Workers in this 
provincial capital yesterday staged a protest march in demand of 
wage hikes and to complain about reductions in their salaries. 
The 500 workers also continued to collect signatures for a 
petition rejecting an adjustment bill, to be presented to 
trustee Juan Schiaretti on 20 March, that sparked violent riots 
here late last year. Union sources said that teachers were 
upset about differences in salaries paid to staff doing the same 
job. The sources added that there is no salary scale to go by 
in the province for teachers and other state workers. Teachers 
unions also said that the 20 percent bonus paid to teachers with 
more than 20 years on the job had been cancelled by the 
government here. 

</TEXT>

