<F P=100> Bolivia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Cited </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2802141494 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1100 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> PY2802141494 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] La Paz, 25 Feb (EFE) -- Bolivian Foreign Minister 
Antonio Aranibar today said that the violent death of Spanish 
citizen Manuel Ramon Puchol in Bolivia has nothing to do with 
the Bolivian Government or people. 
  Aranibar told ANF [Fides News Agency] that his ministry will 
"investigate the real cause" of the death of Puchol, who died on 
10 February in San Matias, Bolivia. 
  The foreign minister said he spoke today with Spanish 
Foreign 
Minister Javier Solana "to whom I expressed our regrets and 
guaranteed the Bolivian Government's political will to clarify 
this murder." 
  According to witnesses, Puchol, 33, died on 10 February in 
San Matias, after being beaten by a group of military men. 
According to a preliminary Bolivian police report, he died as 
consequence of a drug overdose. The police promised to continue 
investigating. 

</TEXT>

