<F P=100> Bolivia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Reportage on Economic Activities </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2402213494 </F>
<F P=103> PY2402213494 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on economic activities in Bolivia through 24 February: 
  Jack Keenan, National Oil Engineering Directorate manager, 
has reported that proven natural gas reserves total 5 trillion 
cubic feet, which guarantees its supply to Brazil, Argentina and 
other markets. Keenan also said current oil reserves guarantee 
the domestic supply for the upcoming 15 years. (La Paz LA RAZON 
in Spanish 11 Feb 94 p A16) 
  Pablo Zavaleta, state general accounting under secretary, 
has 
reported that 76 percent of the economic area budget is 
earmarked for paying the foreign debt. The Finance Ministry 
allocated 896.4 million bolivianos to meet the debt service in 
the first 10 months of 1993. (La Paz LA RAZON in Spanish 12 Feb 
94 p B2) 
  The Multilateral Investments Fund, under the jurisdiction of 
the Inter-American Development Bank, will grant a $2.3 million 
loan to various Bolivian state-owned companies to finance 
programs designed to promote private investments. (Madrid EFE in 
Spanish 2154 GMT 15 Feb 94) 

</TEXT>

