<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Former President Says Economic Plan Will Harm Military </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2802162994 Sao Paulo GAZETA MERCANTIL in Portuguese 25 Feb 
94 p 9 </F>

<F P=103> PY2802162994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sao Paulo GAZETA MERCANTIL </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by Jorge de Freitas from Rio de Janeiro] </F>
  [Excerpts] Former President of the Republic Joao Baptista 
de Oliveira Figueiredo, who was in office from 1979 and 1985, 
said on 24 February during a barbecue at the Freight Companies 
Union in Rio de Janeiro, that the country is risking a social 
upheaval. "When the people are strong, no Armed Forces can 
resist them," he said. Figueiredo criticized Finance Minister 
Fernando Henrique Cardoso's economic plan, saying there will be 
huge loss of purchasing power. [passage omitted] 
  Figueiredo said he will support General Newton Cruz' 
candidacy for Rio de Janeiro governorship. Gen. Cruz headed the 
National Intelligence Service central agency during Figueiredo's 
presidency. Cruz will run for Rio de Janeiro governorship as a 
Democratic Social Party candidate. 

</TEXT>

