<F P=100> Chile </F>
<H3> <TI>   Diplomatic Relations With Cambodia Reestablished </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2402174794 Santiago EL MERCURIO in Spanish 17 Feb 94 p C2 </F>
<F P=103> PY2402174794 </F>
<F P=104>  Santiago EL MERCURIO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] The Chilean Foreign Ministry has reported that a 
ceremony was held at the Chilean mission before the United 
Nations on 16 February, during which Chile and Cambodia resumed 
diplomatic relations at ambassadorial level after a 20-year 
severance. 
  The agreement was signed by Juan Somavia, the Chilean 
permanent representative before the United Nations, and Prince 
Sisowath Sirirath [name and title as published], his Cambodian 
counterpart. [passage omitted] 
  Both countries severed diplomatic relations 20 years ago. 
  A communique released by the Chilean Foreign Ministry states 
that notwithstanding this, "Chile condemned the invasion of 
Cambodia by Vietnam and supported all initiatives to disarm the 
feuding factions and re-establish a peaceful coexistence." 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

