<H3> <TI>   ANDINA Suspends Operations for Lack of Funds </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2702235994 Lima Global de Television Network in Spanish 
0100 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2702235994 </F>
<F P=104>  Lima Global de Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Global TV News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The state-run news agency ANDINA has suspended 
services indefinitely due to a lack of liquid funds. The ANDINA 
board of directors issued a communique announcing that overdue 
accounts have kept the agency from having the necessary liquid 
funds to maintain operations. ANDINA was financed through the 
sale of advertising space to state enterprises. One of the 
agency's main debtors is SUNAT [National Superintendency of Tax 
Administration], which owes ANDINA more than 1 million new soles. 
  ANDINA Information Manager Francisco Perleche said that 
until 
the liquidity problem is resolved, employees will continue doing 
internal work. 

</TEXT>

