<F P=100> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Economic Reports </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2502160794 </F>
<F P=103> PY2502160794 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on economic activities in Peru monitored through 17 
February. 
  The auction of the Ilo copper processing plant was suspended 
on 2 February after the three companies that won the 
international bid declined to submit their offers in the face of 
the $70 million base price proposed by the government. They also 
were compelled to make a $20 million minimum investment. (Lima 
LA REPUBLICA in Spanish 3 Feb 94 p 8) 
  The Economy and Finance Ministry on 11 February assumed 
responsibility for the total foreign medium- and long-range debt 
of National Telecommunications Enterprise Peru, Entel Peru, as a 
step to its privatization, which will begin on 28 February. So 
far there are five consortiums interested in buying Entel and 
the Peruvian Telephone Company, CPT. The base price is $525 
million, of which $190 million will be used to increase CPT's 
capital and the remainder will be divided between CPT and Entel. 
(Lima EXPRESO in Spanish 12 Feb 94 p A23) 

</TEXT>

