<F P=102>  PA0103025994 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 1730 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0103025994 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "National Newscast"] </F>
  [Text] President Cesar Gaviria initiated an official visit 
to Japan today. Early this morning he met with leading financial 
officials to attract Far East investors to our country. 
  President Gaviria's agenda for the first day of his official 
visit to Japan was tight and very productive. During a meeting 
with the Japanese financial sector, the Colombian president and 
the members of his cabinet emphasized economic and security 
advances achieved by the country in past years. They tried to 
convince Japanese investors of the benefits offered by Colombia 
in the business sector. 
  On another topic, Gaviria asked Japan to reduce its tariff 
barriers and to reconsider its restrictions to the import of 
Colombian flowers. Japanese Government officials and media have 
viewed the Colombian president's visit favorably and expect it 
will yield positive results for both countries. 

