<F P=101> Argentina </F>
<H3> <TI>   Exports To Brazil Set `Historical Record' in Dec </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2502214794 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>
<F P=103> PY2502214794 </F>
<F P=104>  -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>



<TEXT>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] Buenos Aires LA NACION in Spanish on 7 
February publishes, on page 13, a 220-word unattributed article 
on Argentine exports to Brazil, which totaled $266.2 million in 
December, "the highest historical record registered in bilateral 
trade relations in one month." It notes that this represents an 
increase of 125 percent compared with the same month in 1991. 
The article says that exports totaled $2.634 billion and 
imports $3.661 billion in 1993, which represents a $1.026 
billion surplus for Brazil but a drop of 23 percent compared 
with 1992. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

