<H3> <TI>   New Ambassador to Mexico Presents Credentials </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0103171594 Havana Radio Progreso Network in Spanish 1200 
GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0103171594 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Progreso Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At a ceremony at Los Pinos, the official residence 
of Mexican President Carlos Salinas de Gortari, Salinas received 
the credentials of Cuba's new ambassador to Mexico, Abelardo 
Curbelo. 
  In statements to the press, Curbelo stressed the Cuban 
Government's interest in expanding ties with Mexico. Curbelo 
said: We must work at finding formulas for doing this. 
  He said, further: It is necessary to develop existing 
agreements between the two nations and seek ways to expand them, 
especially in areas of mutual interest such as tourism and 
industry, along with a greater presence of Mexican capital in 
Cuba. 

</TEXT>

