<H3> <TI>   Venezuelan Delegation Signs Cooperation Accords </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0103204194 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1800 
GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0103204194 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Passages within quotation marks recorded] </F>
  [Text] The visit by a Venezuelan delegation from Cojedes 
State, headed by its governor, Jose Felipe Machado, concludes 
today. The last official activity of the delegation was the 
signing of accords and a sister cities act. 
  Three letters of intent regarding exchanges and cooperation 
between Cojedes and Cuba on health, sports, and housing were 
signed by Governor Machado and Cuban authorities from the 
respective spheres at a ceremony held this morning at the seat 
of the National Assembly of the People's Government. After the 
signing, Machado pointed out the importance of this event: 
  "These mutual cooperation accords will allow me, as governor 
of Cojedes State, to solve many problems which the science and 
resources available there cannot solve. I am pleased with the 
support and cooperation from the Cuban Government, all its 
mid-level authorities, and deputies for their kindness, support, 
and efforts to seal the unity of the people today. The unity of 
the people is sealed with deeds, with realities, with good 
things." 
  The five-day trip ends today. The delegation includes 
members 
of the governor's office and Professor Filipio Duran, vice 
director of the Latin American University. 
  "What I take to my people and country are the good things 
you 
have here in terms of health, sports, and housing construction." 
  A document was signed decreeing sister city status between 
Cojedes and Boyeros Municipality. 

</TEXT>

