<H3> <TI>   Union Leader Urges Reforms To Boost Nickel Industry </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0103044694 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1800 
GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0103044694 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The secretary general of the National Chemical, 
Mining, Energy Industry Workers Trade Union analyzed how the 
economic problems the country is facing have had an effect on 
the nickel industry and have limited its potential. At the same 
time, he acknowledged the sustained effort of the work 
collectives to place the industry on a path to steady recovery. 
  During a meeting with representatives of the National 
Chemical, Mining, Energy Industry Workers Trade Union, he called 
for the prompt introduction of an important program of 
organizational, labor, and wage reforms from the administrative 
directives to boost the recovery of the industry and achieve a 
greater interest by workers in the results of their activity. 

