<F P=100> Caribbean Affairs </F>
<F P=101> Dominican Republic </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fire at Fuel Storage Center Kills 3 Near Haitian Border </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0103232094 Madrid EFE in Spanish 2153 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0103232094 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Santo Domingo, 1 Mar (EFE) -- Today, authorities 
said three persons died and another person suffered serious 
burns following a fire at a house that operated as a gasoline 
warehouse in Dajabon City, bordering Haiti. 
  The deceased, Dominican brothers Ramon and Ovidio Taveras, 
and Haitian Leonel Solis, 25, were burned to ashes while Osiris 
Hernandez, 27, was admitted to the regional hospital Jose Maria 
Cabral y Baez in Santiago City with serious burns. 
  The fire occurred at one of the many family homes that have 
been converted to store fuel which is eventually sold in Haiti. 
Many residents in the border city of Dajabon earn their living 
selling gasoline by taking advantage of the current embargo 
against neighboring Haiti. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

