<H3> <TI>   Oil Tanker Reportedly To Arrive 2 Mar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0103230194 Port-au-Prince Radio Tropic FM in Creole 1300 
GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0103230194 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Tropic FM </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Creole </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] We have learned from a generally well-informed 
source that there will be fuel aplenty in Port-au-Prince. A ship 
carrying several thousand gallons of gasoline and oil -- not 
limited to humanitarian purposes this time --will arrive in 
Port-au-Prince on 2 March to supply the local market. This 
tanker, carrying more fuel than the two humanitarian fuel ships 
that were unloaded in the capital, left The Netherlands bound 
for Haiti and has put in at Aruba, according to the source, who 
adds that a gallon of gasoline will cost $5 in the gas stations 
in Port-au-Prince. 

</TEXT>

