<H3> <TI>   Labor Leader Says Government Forming Paramilitary Groups </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0103143494 Guatemala City PRENSA LIBRE in Spanish 28 Feb 
94 p 16 </F>

<F P=103> PA0103143494 </F>
<F P=104>  Guatemala City PRENSA LIBRE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The government is forming paramilitary groups to 
insert them into labor movements demanding wage increases so as 
to create destabilization, Luis Lara, leader of the National 
Assembly of Health Workers, stated on 27 February. 
  We know of the government's intentions to arm paramilitary 
groups to hinder the movement, but we will remain alert, Lara 
added. 
  Lara was interviewed while heading a protest march. He also 
said the National Assembly of Health Employees will conduct an 
analytical and scientific study to determine the causes of the 
death of patient Miriam Catalina Rodriguez de Alvizurez outside 
the emergency ward of Roosevelt Hospital. 
  Lara said he agrees with other union leaders who have said 
the president of the Republic and the Army commanding general 
are directly responsible for the patient's death. 

