<F P=100> Honduras </F>
<H3> <TI>   Central Bank Lowers Legal Reserve </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0103224594 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 0119 GMT 18 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0103224594 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] Honduran Central Bank President Daniel 
Figueroa has announced that the legal reserve, the highest in 
Central America, has been reduced from 36 to 34 percent for the 
banking system and from 17 to 15 percent for savings and loan 
associations. This reduction will release approximately $15.1 
million into the system and lead to lower interest rates. 
Figueroa said the government intends to keep lowering the legal 
reserve down to between 20 and 25 percent to make it 
competitive. (Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 0119 GMT 18 Feb 94) 

</TEXT>

