<F P=100> Paraguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister on Lifting of Brazilian Customs Bond </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0103181294 Asuncion ABC COLOR in Spanish 27 Feb 94 p 18 </F>
<F P=103> PY0103181294 </F>
<F P=104>  Asuncion ABC COLOR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Paraguayan Foreign Minister Luis Maria Ramirez 
Boettner told ABC COLOR on 26 February that the decision of 
Brazilian customs officials to eliminate the 300 percent bond 
that Paraguayan imports had to pay upon arrival at the Brazilian 
port of Santos for further transfer to Ciudad del Este, was 
greatly influenced by the positive attitude of the Brazilian 
Foreign Ministry, which reacted favorably to a request from its 
Paraguayan counterpart and recommended that the issue be studied. 
  Following two days of negotiations with Paraguayan Customs 
Director General Miguel Angel Britos, who had been sent to 
Brasilia to find a solution to the problem, top officials of the 
Brazilian Federal Revenue (the office in charge of collecting 
custom taxes) announced on 25 February that the 300-percent bond 
on all Paraguayan imports through the port of Santos has been 
eliminated. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

