<F P=100> Venezuela </F>
<H3> <TI>   Emergency Law To Apply to Banco Latino </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2802201594 Caracas Venezolana de Television Network in 
Spanish 1550 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2802201594 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Venezolana de Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From "The News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Gustavo Tarre Briceno, chairman of the Congressional 
Finance Commission, announced that the draft of the emergency 
law that will apply to the Banco Latino case will be ready today. 
  Meanwhile, Gustavo Roosen, president of the bank's 
intervention board, said that the emergency law establishes 
financial aid for Banco Latino, something that will allow the 
implementation this week of strategies for the bank's 
rehabilitation. Roosen explained that the banking law that has 
been in effect since the beginning of this year envisages a 
rehabilitation phase as long as the rules set by the Bank 
Superintendency and the Deposit Guarantee Fund during the 
intervention phase are followed. Roosen said the bank has lost 
150 billion bolivares, an amount that can increase or diminish 
depending on the work carried out by the current intervention 
board. 

</TEXT>

