<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Refuses Comment on Expulsions From Canada </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0103164194 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 1533 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0103164194 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Havana, 1 Mar (NOTIMEX) -- The Cuban Foreign 
Ministry refused to comment today on the alleged expulsion from 
Canada of two Cuban diplomats who worked at that nation's 
consulate in Montreal. 
  A Foreign Ministry source told NOTIMEX the ministry has not 
yet received information in that regard. 
  The newspaper "TORONTO SUN" published on 27 February Cuban 
Consul Adolfo Martin and Vice Consul Orlando Brito were expelled 
in February on charges of espionage. 
  According to the newspaper, Brito was in charge of the Cuban 
intelligence apparatus, while Martin was in charge of helping 
dissidents [opositores] enter Canada. 

