<H3> <TI>   Envoy to Brazil Concludes Tour of Duty </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0203170794 Havana Radio Progreso Network in Spanish 1200 
GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0203170794 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Progreso Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Brazilian President Itamar Franco has bestowed upon 
Cuban Ambassador Jorge Bolanos Brazil's highest distinction, the 
Great Cross of the Cruzeiro do Sul Order. In a ceremony at the 
Foreign Ministry in Brasilia, Foreign Minister Celso Amorim 
presented the medal to the Cuban diplomat, who has just 
concluded his tour of duty in Brazil. In his address Bolanos 
stated that he is returning to Havana with the satisfaction of 
seeing relations between the two nations on a broad and 
irreversible path of development; and he praised Brazil's 
foreign policy, which he described as dynamic and rooted in the 
best traditions of justice, peace, and respect for the 
sovereignty and self-determination of peoples. 

