<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Views Complex Economic Situation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0203230494 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 2030 GMT 
2 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0203230494 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Jose Luis Rodriguez Garcia, minister president of 
the State Committee for Finance, has explained the country's 
complex economic situation and the efforts being made to bail 
the country out of the current crisis. 
  Speaking during a national training seminar for higher 
education teachers, Rodriguez Garcia said the country at this 
moment has more than 145,000 self-employed workers, and that 
this figure is increasing. He added that the measures adopted in 
the wake of dissolution of the socialist countries and the U.S. 
imperialist blockade have had an economic, political, and social 
cost. 
  During the seminar, postgraduate education was discussed, 
during which it was agreed that experts must be integrated to 
enhance their professional level and the prestige of the 
university center. 

</TEXT>

