<H3> <TI>   Lieutenant Arrested in Death of Spanish Citizen </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0203204994 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1628 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> PY0203204994 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] La Paz, 2 Mar (EFE) -- Bolivian sources have 
reported that Bolivian Army Lieutenant Marco Antonio Mejia 
Alarcon was detained today, accused of murdering Spanish citizen 
Manuel Ramon Puchol Pastor. 
  Puchol, 33, a Spanish judicial branch employee, died on 10 
February in San Matias. 
  According to several witnesses and a medical report, the 
Spanish citizen was beaten to death by a group of military men. 
The La Paz Government maintained until today the version that 
he had died of a cocaine overdose or that he had committed 
suicide. 

</TEXT>

