<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Franco Completes Cabinet Reshuffling </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0303013494 Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network in Portuguese 
2200 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0303013494 </F>
<F P=104>  Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Itamar Franco has just finished 
reshuffling his cabinet. A short time ago Planalto Palace 
announced that General Rubens Bayma Denys, head of the Military 
Command of the East, will head the Transportation Ministry, 
replacing Minister Margarita Coimbra. 
  Presidential Press Secretary Francisco Baker has just 
announced that President Itamar Franco has decided to maintain 
acting Minister Eleonor Franco as head of the Social Welfare 
Ministry, and acting Minister Guillermo Morais as head of the 
Communications Ministry. 
  According to Baker, Israel Vargas will stay at the Science 
and Technology Ministry; Senator Beni Veras of the PSDB 
[Brazilian Social Democracy Party] of Ceara is the new planning 
minister; and Alexis Stepanenko is the new mines and energy 
minister. 
  Lastly, Francisco Baker said that President Itamar Franco 
has 
nominated Deputy Aluizio Alves of the PMDB [Brazilian Democratic 
Movement Party] of Rio Grande do Norte to head the Ministry of 
Regional Integration. He had been proposed for the post by the 
PMDB. 
  Minister Romildo Caim will stay at the Federal 
Administration 
Secretariat. The new ministers will be installed next week 
after President Itamar Franco's return from Venezuela. 

</TEXT>

