<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Governor Brizola Seeks Alliance With PMDB </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0303003694 Sao Paulo FOLHA DE SAO PAULO in Portuguese 27 
Feb 94 Section 1 p 14 </F>

<F P=103> PY0303003694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sao Paulo FOLHA DE SAO PAULO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] [Rio de Janeiro] Governor Leonel Brizola (PDT) 
[Democratic Labor Party] is looking to the PMDB [Brazilian 
Democratic Movement Party] as the only party with which he might 
break the isolation of his candidacy for the presidency of the 
Republic. He is acting on two fronts, seeking to convince at 
least some PMDB members. He is openly courting the PMDB's Rio 
Grande do Sul State wing, while quietly and favorably responding 
to former [Sao Paulo] Governor Orestes Quercia's overtures for 
agreement. 
  Brizola's isolation stems from the unfeasibility of an 
alliance with the PT [Workers Party] -- owing to the absolute 
leadership of Lula [PT leader Luis Inacio Da Silva] in the polls 
and the consequent reluctance of the latter -- and with the PSDB 
[Brazilian Social Democracy Party], mainly because of his 
aversion to the party's Ceara State wing. 
  In light of the affinity expressed by PPR [Progressive 
Renewal Party] leader Paulo Maluf, who is sympathetic toward 
Brizola, with [Bahia Governor] Antonio Carlos Magalhaes' PFL 
[Liberal Front Party] -- which is the PDT's worst enemy after 
entrepreneur Roberto Marinho -- it has been said that the 
possibility of an alliance has definitely been buried, leaving 
the PMDB as the only alternative. 
  Brizola has already met with PMDB President Luiz Henrique da 
Silveira once and will meet him again this week. Brizola 
proposes using his political clout in Rio Grande do Sul State to 
help former [Social Security] Minister Antonio Britto become the 
Rio Grande do Sul governor in exchange for support for his 
presidential candidacy. 
  Brizola even pledged to overcome old disagreements with 
Senator Pedro Simon in order to reach an understanding. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-10188 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drlat042_m_94005" </HT>


