<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Salinas Cited on Optimism Over Chiapas Dialogue </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0303042794 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 0000 
GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0303042794 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Radio ACIR Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Elisa Betias Otero; from the "ACIR Radio News" </F>
newscast] 
  [Excerpt] I would like to report that President Carlos 
Salinas de Gortari indicated this afternoon that his 
administration is unflinchingly taking on the commitments agreed 
during the process for peace and justice taking place in 
Chiapas. He also announced that the necessary decisions to 
guarantee the execution of these commitments will be made in the 
next few days. 
  The president expressed his optimism with the conclusion of 
the peace and reconciliation talks in Chiapas and he indicated 
that the dialogue has already provided evidence of positive 
results. In this respect, he called for the support of society 
in order to reach to the signing of a peace agreement. 
  The president's statements were made public through a 
communique issued by the Presidency of the Republic. The 
communique stresses that the list of demands presented to the 
government through Peace Commissioner Manuel Camacho was 
acknowledged with the true disposition of listening and solving 
the Indians' demands for justice, welfare, and dignity. 
  With regard to the letter the communique points out that the 
government has decided to seriously honor its commitments and 
that the necessary decisions to ensure the execution of said 
commitments will be made in the next few days. We expect 
society's support on the points agreed upon and that by backing 
these points we will all be looking out to ensure that all 
details are honored which will allow us to reach to the signing 
of a final peace agreement. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

