<F P=100> El Salvador </F>
<H3> <TI>   Poll Predicts ARENA Election Victory </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0203213694 San Salvador Radio Cadena YSU in Spanish 1800 
GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0203213694 </F>
<F P=104>  San Salvador Radio Cadena YSU </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "National Events" newscast] </F>
  [Text] According to all polls held in this country, the 
Nationalist Republican Alliance [ARENA] will win the 20 March 
elections. Rene Figueroa, of ARENA, has said that the voters' 
intentions to favor this organization are very clear and that 
this tendency is growing as elections day draws closer. 
  [Begin Figueroa recording] Looking at our own polls and at 
those carried out by the University of Central America [UCA] we 
find that it is clear that the electoral preferences for the 
presidential ticket made up of Armando Calderon Sol and Enrique 
Borgo Bustamante indicates that the ARENA candidates are sure 
first round winners. 
  The trend is clear, the backing of the Salvadoran people is 
clear, the intentions of the Salvadoran voters are clear. 
Another conclusion we have reached is that the Christian 
Democratic Party and the National Convergence-Farabundo Marti 
National Liberation Front [FMLN] coalition are competing for a 
distant, very distant, second place. We want to make this 
clear. Our polls and those of UCA indicate this. 
  We have reached the conclusion that as we approach election 
day, the support for ARENA grows while the support for the 
Christian Democratic Party and for the National Convergence-FMLN 
coalition remains unchanged. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

