<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Political Alliance Formed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94P20433D </F>
<F P=103> 94P20433D </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:CSO 

  [Editorial Report] Managua LA PRENSA in Spanish of 5 
February 1994 on pages 1 and 14 reports that Adolfo Calero 
Portocarrero, vice president of the National Conservative Party 
(PNC), announced the formation of the Blue and White Triangle, a 
political alliance joining the conservative and liberal parties 
and the Nicaraguan Resistance. Calero explained that the 
alliance responds to "the wishes of the rank and file." Calero 
stated: "The rank and file will follow the conservative/liberal 
party which shows the most leadership...." The strongest parties 
in the National Opposition Union are the Liberal 
Constitutionalist Party, the Liberal Independent Party, and the 
PNC, according to the article. PNC official Rina Cardenal 
announced that each party within the alliance will hold 
primaries and then "the rank and file will elect their true 
representatives." 

</TEXT>

