<F P=100> Haiti </F>
<H3> <TI>   Confederation of 130 Grassroots Organizations Meets </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0203214194 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1130 
GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0203214194 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Nearly 130 people's organizations, which met at 
Le Palace Hotel on 27 February, created the Confederation of 
Haitian People's Organizations for Development [COPHADEV]. 
According to its general coordinator, Jean-Saurel Beaujour, the 
organization's purpose is to work toward alleviating the 
economic and political stagnation in which Haiti is plunged. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

